decision_conditions:
Condition : 6 - The use and/or development hereby approved shall operate at all times to meet the following standards:
(i)  	Noise from any plant or machinery shall not exceed 5dB(A) below the existing background noise level when measured at the boundary of the nearest noise-sensitive property;
(ii) 	Air extracted from the food cooking air must pass through a filtration system. In addition, simple grease traps and activated carbon filters (or some other approved odour removal technology) shall be incorporated into the design to minimise the likelihood of cooking odours being present in the exhausted air;
(iii)  	Flexible couplings and anti-vibration mountings shall be used on all surface mounted plans that generates noise or vibrations to prevent the transmission of noise and vibration into any adjoining property.
Reason: In order to protect neighbours' living conditions.
